docs.abstract: In the months since Mr. Arbery was shot to death, Brunswick, Ga., has been focused on issues of racial inequality.
docs.snippet: In the months since Mr. Arbery was shot to death, Brunswick, Ga., has been focused on issues of racial inequality.
docs.lead_paragraph: BRUNSWICK, Ga. — As jury selection in the trial of the three men accused of killing Ahmaud Arbery began last week, a group of clergy gathered outside the Glynn County courthouse. They handed out rainbow stickers that read: “Do justice. Love mercy. Walk humbly … together.” They prayed for Mr. Arbery’s family, for the families of the defendants and for their community.

headline.main: As the Trial in Ahmaud Arbery’s Killing Nears, a Community Is on Edge
headline.print_headline: Community on Edge as the Trial for Arbery’s Killing Nears

docs.abstract: A growing number of forensic researchers are questioning how the field interprets the geographic ancestry of human remains.
docs.snippet: A growing number of forensic researchers are questioning how the field interprets the geographic ancestry of human remains.
docs.lead_paragraph: Racial reckonings were happening everywhere in the summer of 2020, after George Floyd was killed in Minneapolis by the police. The time felt right, two forensic anthropologists reasoned, to reignite a conversation about the role of race in their own field, where specialists help solve crimes by analyzing skeletons to determine who those people were and how they died.

headline.main: Can Skeletons Have a Racial Identity?
headline.print_headline: Can Skeletons Have a Racial Identity?

docs.abstract: He was chased and shot to death on a residential street. But will a jury rule that he was murdered?
docs.snippet: He was chased and shot to death on a residential street. But will a jury rule that he was murdered?
docs.lead_paragraph: In the coming days, a trial will begin to determine whether the fatal shooting of Ahmaud Arbery, an unarmed Black man, by two armed white men is considered murder under Georgia state law. Today, we explore why that may be a difficult case for prosecutors to make.

headline.main: The Trial Over Ahmaud Arbery’s Killing
